# pyenv
#   For a library or package, you might want to ignore these files since the Python version
#   is managed by the developer. For a binary/application that is locked to a specific
#   Python version, you might want to check these, and the .python-version file, into source control.
# .python-version

# pipenv
#   According to pypa/pipenv#598, it is recommended to include Pipfile.lock in version control.
#   However, in case of collaboration, if having platform-specific dependencies or dependencies
#   having cross-platform versions, pipenv install will force the dependencies to be installed
#   based on the Pipfile.lock, ignoring the platform differences.
# Pipfile.lock

venv/
.env